Day 3 Session 1: Conditional statements — if, elif, else

- if runs when condition is True
- elif checks a second condition if the first is False
- else runs when nothing above is True
- Indentation is not optional — it defines what belongs inside each block
- and requires both conditions to be True
- or requires at least one condition to be True
- Conditionals make code intelligent — it responds to data values

## Reflection  Session 2

- Conditionals classify real data into meaningful categories
- Multiple elif levels create detailed classification systems
- Combining scores into an average then classifying gives an overall picture
- Boolean variables work directly in if statements without comparison operators
- String comparisons work the same way as number comparisons
- Every marine parameter can be given a threshold and classified automatically
